article.headline: Nicholls St. 60, Cent. Arkansas 51
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Ryan Bathie went 3-for-5 on 3-pointers, snared 9 rebounds and scored 19 points Saturday to lead Nicholls State to a 60-51 victory over Central Arkansas. The Colonels (9-20, 4-10 Southland Conference) got 14 points from a pair of players -- Adonis Gray and Dominic Friend -- and Friend also grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds for a double-double. Anatoly Bose added 10 points for Nicholls. Nicholls led 30-22 at the half. Marcus Pillow topped the offense for UCA (14-15, 4-11) with 19 points on 4-for-6 shooting from long distance. Nate Bowie scored 15 for the Bears and York Sims added 10.
